snippet.textDisplay:
Tbh I don't particularly like this song but I listen to it bcoz it reminds me of my coaching days in 12th class back in 2021. I had a dear female friend who was more than just a friend to me, she was my favourite person & still is. We would catch up every day at coaching &she was such a kind & sweet soul. We had a strong bond & one day she told me she loved listening to this song, so I added it to my playlist.
After we completed our schooling, we stayed in touch for a while but suddenly out of nowhere she stopped reaching to me. I've missed her every day since then. Today is her birthday & I swear I saw her in my dream for the first time in a long while. That's why I am listening to this song again indulging in nostalgia.
Man she's truly a wonderful person, and I wish her all the best. May good things come her way, and may she be blessed with happiness ❤🤲

snippet.textDisplay:
Some memories render me overwhelmed,
Restless, as though I can't escape their hold,
A storm of thoughts that swirl and swell,
In every echo, a story untold.

They linger like shadows in the quiet night,
Whispers of moments once filled with light,
Now they rise, unbidden and wild,
Leaving me lost, like a forgotten child.

Yet within this tempest, I find a grace,
A tender trace of an old embrace,
For though these memories pull me apart,
They are woven deep within my heart.

So I let them come, as they always do,
For in the stillness, I will find something true,
A piece of me, both shattered and whole,
A journey of growth, within my soul.
